column5: Hi all, I am relatively new to fishing and I love it. I need to find a place to fish close to Toronto. There is just Rice lake and Oak lakes that I am familiar with. Are there any other options in and around Toronto/GTA that might be worth a visit.  Please help...  Cheers
Try the Toronto Islands. There are many species like pike, carp, bass, etc...
Ohhhh I can see how you're nicks are going to confuse the hell outta me...  G
Thanks guys will definitely try it out.  Cheers and enjoy da summer !
Da boys have nearly da same nicks.... peace out homies  G
I'm confused  Can the "old" new angler change his name to "somewhat new angler"!
